Results
Among 148 SBA patients, seven received CPI therapy. The objective response rate (ORR) was 86%, with one (14%) complete response (CR) and five (71%) partial responses (PR). Median progression-free survival (mPFS) was 31 months (mFU:32 months); median overall survival (mOS) was not reached (mFU: 33 months). Overall, 55% underwent MMR testing, and 18% of SBA patients were dMMR.
Conclusion
