This study proposes that LibQUAL should evolve to include a fourth dimension focused on AI services. This future-ready addition would enable libraries to assess the quality of AI-driven offerings, gather targeted feedback from users, identify service gaps and implement iterative improvements. Despite widespread AI adoption, no existing opinion piece or framework has thoroughly addressed the need for updating LibQUAL to reflect this AI shift.
